  • Package antworld.common

    • Class antworld.common.AntAction extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      20170504L

      • Serialized Fields

        • type

          AntAction.AntActionType type

        • direction

          Direction direction
          One of the 8 possible directions. The AntActionTypes requiring Direction are: MOVE, ATTACK, PICKUP, DROP, HEAL (when OUT_AND_ABOUT). Set to null to indicate a self-heal or self-attack.

        • x

          int x
          (x,y) specify absolute coordinates in the Ant World grid. These fields are only used by the EXIT_NEST action. An EXIT_NEST action is only valid when the specified coordinates are within a Manhattan Distance of Constants.NEST_RADIUS from the ant's own nest center and, of course, when the ant is underground.

        • y

          int y
          (x,y) specify absolute coordinates in the Ant World grid. These fields are only used by the EXIT_NEST action. An EXIT_NEST action is only valid when the specified coordinates are within a Manhattan Distance of Constants.NEST_RADIUS from the ant's own nest center and, of course, when the ant is underground.

        • quantity

          int quantity
          Specifies a quantity needed by the PICKUP and DROP ant actions. Set by the server after a MOVE action to give the ticks remaining before that ant may take any other action.

    • Class antworld.common.AntData extends GameObject implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      20170504L

      • Serialized Fields

        • nestName

          NestNameEnum nestName
          The name of the nest to which this ant belongs.

        • teamName

          TeamNameEnum teamName
          The name of the team to which this ant belongs.

        • id

          int id
          Unique id. When the client uses the birth action to create an ant, the client should leave this set to the default value of Constants.UNKNOWN_ANT_ID.

          When the server accepts an ant's birth action, the server sets the id to a unique value that monotonically increases with the tick.

        • state

          AntAction.AntState state

        • antType

          AntType antType
          The ant objType.

        • carryUnits

          int carryUnits
          The number of food units the ant is carrying. An ant may carry either food or water.
          The maximum number of units an ant can carry is given by this.antType.getCarryCapacity()

        • carryType

          GameObject.GameObjectType carryType
          Ants cannot carry ants. The only valid carryType values are: WATER and FOOD.

        • action

          AntAction action
          The client sets myAction to tell the server what the ant wants to do. The server returns this set to the action that was actually taken.

        • health

          int health
          This ant's health. When an ant's health reaches 0, it dies.

No two game objects may occupy the same pixel at the same time. NOTE: food being carried by an ant is part of the ant game object.

    • Class antworld.common.PacketToClient extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      20170504L

      • Serialized Fields

        • tick

          int tick
          AntWorld is a real-time game with a minimum time between turns equal to antworld.common.Constants.TIME_STEP_MSEC.
          When the server starts, gameTick = 0. Each time the server sends an update to its set of clients, gameTick is incremented by 1.

        • tickTime

          double tickTime
          Time, in seconds, of the current gameTick.
          This is set using the Java Virtual Machine's high-resolution time source, in nanoseconds. This method provides nanosecond precision, but not necessarily nanosecond resolution (that is, how frequently the value changes) - no guarantees are made except that the resolution is at least as good as that of currentTimeMillis(). This value will becomes unpredictable if the game runs over approximately 292 years.

        • errorMsg

          java.lang.String errorMsg
          If not null, then an error has occurred. Display it!

        • myNest

          NestNameEnum myNest

        • myAntList

          java.util.ArrayList<E> myAntList
          List of ants that belong to this nest.
          When an ant dies, the server will include it in this list (with state==DEAD) only for the next update.

          If an ant's action is NOOP or BUSY for two or more consecutive ticks, it will only be included in myAntList if something about its state changed since the last update when it was included.

        • nestData

          NestData[] nestData
          Nest data for each nest in the game.
          Index this array with:
          nestData[NestNameEnum.ordinal]

          If a nest has not been claimed by a team, then its corresponding element is set to null.
          If there was no change in a particular nest since the last update, then the corresponding element is set to null.

        • enemyAntList

          java.util.ArrayList<E> enemyAntList
          A list of all enemy ants that were visible to one or more of this team's ants during the most recent tick. Note: if none of your ants see any enemy ants, then this is null.

        • foodList

          java.util.ArrayList<E> foodList
          A list of all food piles (including water droplets) that were visible to one or more of this team's ants during the most recent tick. Note: if none of your ants see any food, then this is null.

    • Class antworld.common.PacketToServer extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      20170504L

      • Serialized Fields

        • myTeam

          TeamNameEnum myTeam

        • myAntList

          java.util.ArrayList<E> myAntList
          This list must contain every ant belonging to client that is going to attempt some action in the current timestep.
          The client uses this list to tell the server which of its ants do what.
          There is no need to include ants with the NOOP or BUSY action.

          The server will execute ant actions in the following order:
          1) All actions of all ants from a team are executed before all actions of any team that reported its moves after the this team reported.
          2) Ant actions within a nest are executed in the list order. This is important when one ant needs to move into the space another ant is moving out of or when one ant wants to pick up an item dropped in the same tick by another ant.

          If the client sends a message with myAntList = null, then the server's next reply will include a full list of all ants belonging to the nest. This is useful when the client reconnects after crashing.

        • timeReceived

          double timeReceived
          Time in seconds from the start of the game. This field is set by the server when the message is received.
